# MultiLine Command Fail
# author: Scott Bronson
# date:   3 Dec 2001
#
# We now require commands to fit entirely on a single line.
# It's an error if you don't use the continuation char.
# tmtest used to append all lines to the command until the next dash or comment.

tmtest -o - <<-EOL
	# MultiLine Command Fail
	# author: Scott Bronson
	# date:   3 Dec 2001
	#
	# We now require commands to fit entirely on a single line.
	# It's an error if you don't use the continuation char:

	echo 
		this
		is not
		all on
		one line

	------ STDOUT: exit code 0 - no error
EOL

------ STDERR:
file STDIN line 8: expecting the exit clause. did you forget a continuation character?
    	this

------ STDOUT: exit code 255 - abort!
